i"><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=80</span><=
/a> rad being equal to 360=C2=B0). Degrees are traditionally used in <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Navigation" title=3D"Navigation">navigat=
ion</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surveying" title=3D"Surve=
ying">surveying</a>, and many applied disciplines, while radians are more c=
ommon in mathematics and mathematical <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Physics" title=3D"Physics">physics</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polar_coordinate_syste=
