figure>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archimedean_spiral" title=
=3D"Archimedean spiral">Archimedean spiral</a> is a spiral discovered by <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archimedes" title=3D"Archimedes">Arc=
himedes</a>, which can also be expressed as a simple polar equation. It is =
represented by the equation
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle r(\varphi )=3Da+b\varphi .}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
