4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polar_coord=
inate_system#cite_note-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The angular coordinate <i>=CF=86</i> is expressed in radians through=
out this section, which is the conventional choice when doing calculus.
</p>
