a</i> and <i>=CF=86</i> =3D <i>b</i> such that <span class=3D"texhtml">0 &l=
t; <i>b</i> =E2=88=92 <i>a</i> &lt; 2<i>=CF=80</i></span>. The length of <i=
>L</i> is given by the following integral
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle L=3D\int _{a}^{b}{\sqrt {\left[r(\varphi )\right]^{2}+\left[{\t=
frac {dr(\varphi )}{d\varphi }}\right]^{2}}}d\varphi }">
