ed by <i>n</i>, the number of subintervals. For each subinterval <i>i</i> =
=3D 1, 2, ..., <i>n</i>, let <i>=CF=86</i><sub><i>i</i></sub> be the midpoi=
nt of the subinterval, and construct a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
