sum _{i=3D1}^{n}{\tfrac {1}{2}}r(\varphi _{i})^{2}\,\Delta \varphi .}"></sp=
an>
</p><p>As the number of subintervals <i>n</i> is increased, the approximati=
on of the area improves. Taking <span class=3D"nowrap"><i>n</i> =E2=86=92 =
=E2=88=9E</span>, the sum becomes the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Riemann_sum" title=3D"Riemann sum">Riemann sum</a> for the above integr=
al.
</p><p>A mechanical device that computes area integrals is the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planimeter" title=3D"Planimeter">planimeter</a=
>, which measures the area of plane figures by tracing them out: this repli=
cates integration in polar coordinates by adding a joint so that the 2-elem=
ent <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linkage_(mechanical)" title=3D=
"Linkage (mechanical)">linkage</a> effects <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Green%27s_theorem" title=3D"Green's theorem">Green's theorem</a>, =
converting the quadratic polar integral to a linear integral.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Generalization">Generalizat=
