<p>Using <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cartesian_coordinates" cl=
ass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cartesian coordinates">Cartesian coordinates</=
a>, an infinitesimal area element can be calculated as <i>dA</i> =3D <i>dx<=
/i> <i>dy</i>. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integration_by_=
