an></span></div>
<p>The polar coordinate system is extended into three dimensions with two d=
ifferent coordinate systems, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C=
ylindrical_coordinate_system" title=3D"Cylindrical coordinate system">cylin=
drical</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spherical_coordinat=
e_system" title=3D"Spherical coordinate system">spherical coordinate system=
s</a>, both of which include two-dimensional or planar polar coordinates as=
 a subset. In essence, the cylindrical coordinate system extends polar coor=
dinates by adding an additional distance coordinate, while the spherical sy=
stem instead adds an additional angular coordinate.
</p>
